  "name": "Magnetic Variation and Deviation",
  "type": "871ae771-b9b1-4f40-8c7f-d9038bfb69c3",
  "created": 1774632631356,
  "modified": 1775152992418,
  "content": {
    "description": [
      ":doc",
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Variation"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Magnetic variation is the difference between Magnetic North and True North. Therefore variation = magnetic - true i.e. an Easterly variation is positive and a Westerly variation is negative."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":blockquote",
        [
          ":p",
          {
            "s": "[!info]"
          }
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "°True - variation = °Magnetic"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Deviation"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Deviation is due to local magnetic fields - typically objects on the boat. Deviation varies by compass reading, unlike magnetic variation. "
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Magnetic deviation is the difference between Magnetic North and Compass North. Therefore deviation = magnetic - compass i.e. an Easterly deviation is positive and a Westerly deviation is negative."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":blockquote",
        [
          ":p",
          {
            "s": "[!info]"
          }
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "°Magnetic - deviation = °Compass"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Calculation"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":blockquote",
        [
          ":p",
          {
            "s": "[!tip]"
          }
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Get from °True to °Magnetic to °Compass by subtracting the \"discrepancy\" at each step"
        }
      ]
    ],
